t time I think it was twilight sleep. Yes. Yes. And - it was I who was the one that - but - dad had gone to work and I can remember about half past five or six o'clock in the morning mum talk - calling me, and asking me would I take a letter down to Whitc
h
urch. Llanduth it was really. And - remember going on the - think it was the ten past seven train, and - yes, by train. Yes, for mum. And - Church Road. Yes. Then they brought me, I came up with them then and I know you'd have loved them, we live - when w
e lived in this little street up there, Bryn Terrace, five houses, and having us they were all relatives. See, we were the - but - we were considered - I - it was all granny Em and grandpa Davis. Yes.
