\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well - no - just to - well perhaps after lunch time. My job, you know, I told you ab
out the little dark kitchen, back kitchen which was on the side of the house, you see the other houses had their kitchens - their little back kitchens right at the back. But we were - I think our house had been built on sometime after the rest, and - then
 
we were sort of coming out onto the little country road more than the others, so that they didn't have - the space to build it at the back. And the other little houses had very much more frontage than we had, we just had two tiny back - and I can remember
 
very well on moonlight nights - these people, now the manager of the brickworks, there's a huge brickworks where the new little village is built, Garth Newydd, and - the manager of the brick works - Mr Bodwey came there - came to Wynnstay to live, and - h
i
s daughter and I got very friendly, she was about two years older than I was, but we were still good friends, and her mum and my mum were friends, so perhaps now after our evening meal Mrs Bodwey would come down to have a chat with mum and - Edith and I w
ould sit on the - window sills outside Even in the winter evenings, you know, when it's been moonlight, just watching the - clouds and the moon, I often think I don't know if the children would be satisfied with doing that sort of thing today would they.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No, they're more sophisticated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Cated, yes. Yes. Yes. Mind I - I - I think there's - it's a good thing in some ways but not too much of it, it's gone from one extreme to the other hasn't it. I didn't care for children to go back perhaps quite to o
ur childhood, but - I - I think now they're grown up far too quickly aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 It was very beautiful round here wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh, it's beautiful, and I've always been - somebody, even from a young age to appreciate the beauty you know. Oh lovely
, yes. Yes. And of course living up there you can imagine it was really more beautiful than here, we had so much better view. Could all see the western and - all that you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You had a good climb up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh it was a climb, yes. But still as children you wouldn't notice it would you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 But your mother must have felt it, and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. But of course they were quite young - when they're moving from there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 They were only in their twenties really weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. Yes. And - I was nine, we didn't do our sums quite right. I was - I would have been about nine, not ten when I came down here. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 In about 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. That's right. Mm, so I wasn't - mm. Not far out really, not to make that much difference anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 And you stayed here then until you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. I didn't have a job then except just helping at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Pontypridd - for a very short while. I didn't care for it at all. And - I came - I went then and I 
then went back to Brynn Terrace to live in Auntie Cassie's house - for a while - granny Em dies, and - Auntie Cass sent a message up to ask would we look after her house for a little while - while she arranged something differently 'cos Grandpa Davis was 
failing, she and May moved there to look after him, and we moved right back in Brynn Terrace again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Did you like it there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh loved it, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 And then you came back down here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No, no, we moved - we lived in a house just -
 you don't know the - you don't know the Garth, no. A house belonging to my uncle, that uncle that I was telling that - we - Len and he were such pals. That would be a little bit higher up again than Brynn Terrace. If you go up the Gwaelogs and by the pub
lic house then you look straight up, there are two double fronted houses. Very pleasant looking houses, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You went up there for a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh until we came down here, yes. I came down, I told you about my brother, didn't I, being an epilept
ic. Yes. He was - he had meningitis when he was about - eleven months old, when I was - just after I started school at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 Pontypridd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
. And the sad part about it you see being kept at home until he was thirty see well it wasn't so easy to get - them to - into -
 into institutions was it, and - anyway I don't think my mother - mum wouldn't have let him go, it would have to come to - you know, that we - you know, that we couldn't manage. But it was a sad thing really because he could have been - taught to have don
e
 such a lot. You see, we brought him up as a baby, couldn't speak, he was speaking - saying quite a few words, he used to - call me when I'd be coming home from school, Etta you know, and look - all the little baby words, because he lost his speech. But s
ome of his - cell - br}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
ins that was all perfect, like his hearing, his memory, and a certain reasoning you know, I don't suppose all his reasoning, but of course with him being - not speaking we assumed that he was much - worse than what he was. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 And you were doing everything for him then probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Yes, feeding him and all, it was so unnecessary. Because - as soon as they had a nurse they taught him to feed himself. And to go to the toilet. He didn't actually come that he could - like actual
ly see to himself, but they taught him as much that he'd go to fetch one of them to take him. Well look at the help that would have been for us at home wouldn't it have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Even when you were young you were helping to look after him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. Yes. Well
 that's all I really knew in the home was perhaps trying to scrap and do a bit of homework and - then take - you know, Llewellyn out you see for a walk, over the woods usually here, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Could he walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Only until he was - no, he didn't walk at 
all until he was seven. I used to carry him Welsh fashion in a Shawl, yes, until he was quite a big age. And - I know it caused - there was a bit of bad feeling between my aunt - my aunt - was living in the house next door and they moved to - to Penarth, 
a
nd I know - she was very cross with mum, she thought that I was doing too much. But I think with mum it had got in the end that - Llewellyn was first with everything And I know very many times I'd come to the back gate there with him about nine o'clock, I
'd tell the girls, oh I'll see you - have a little game of rounders or - cricket with the boys even, I didn't mind anything, only just have a game, and - but if it was light mam would - I'd have to go back and take him out, keep him out a bit longer. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Well - I can never remember - looking - over it now, I think I felt a little bit more bitterness about it, knowing what I'd missed, you know, than I - I can never really remember being bitter about things you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You would never say oh I won't do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Oh no. I - I don't think I ever said anything like that to my mother 'til she - when she died even. I respected my mother too much you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You must have been a wonderful temperament?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well I - I - oh I don't suppose -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What about the others in the family, did they do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
No, no, very much - both my sisters were very good, but my sister would speak - the one - the middle one, would speak up for herself more, you know. She'd do a certain am
ount, but then she'd just tell mam she was going out. But I suppose being that much younger and those few years perhaps made a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You felt more responsible probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What about the other children in the village, what did they think about you having the little brother, having to mind him all the time?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
I never discussed it very much with - you know, with them. Really. I know they - some of them were very patient and would come and call for me and - you know, and of course o
ur home - in the beginning before Lennie - 'cos he looked just like an ordinary - he was a very good looking boy mind, even when he died, now - there was nothing repulsive about him at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 He wasn't a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 Mongol}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589  or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No. No. No. No. And - h
e was exceptionally good looking but then - you know, he was really good looking, beautiful skin, lovely big blue eyes, and fair wavy hair you know, and you can tell, he didn't even look mental until the fits - start - the - he wasn't having fits, and the
y were working inwardly and I think that sort of made him that you could sort of tell, but as I - there's something about somebody mentally retarded isn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 There's a sort of vacancy isn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes, that's it. And yet he didn't have that v
acant look. Not what they were - because I tell you I remember one time mother was very hurt - the laundry boy was coming up like just used to take dad's - couple of collars, 'cos mam did all the washing and - just a few collars or something, and perhaps 
a
 best tablecloth, the - the big ones you know or something like that, and - Linnie was - just on the front there, and - he - he gave him the message you see and - he wasn't answering him and of course had swore at him, and I don't know what he didn't call
 
him you know. But of course not knowing - I'm just mentioning this to you for you to realize that he wasn't - and then if we took him for walks over the wood and he went a little bit in front of us and there were visitors, because he used to be oh - hundr
e
ds of visitors, I could hon - honestly say hundreds of visitors in the summer, you wouldn't be able to see the front of the mountain - for visitors, and they'd ask him the way and all that, you see - so you can - he couldn't answer or anything. No. But - 
and oh they loved him down in Hensall. He - they really loved him, he was that nice - 'cos it's like everything else isn't it, if they're naughty and they - you - you can't have quite the same love for them can you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Some of them have lovely dispositions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 Dispositions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 , and he did. Yes. He did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 When you say there were hundreds of visitors, come to look at the scenery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Up on the mountain picnicking and - you know. Yes. Oh very popular, and there was the Colliers Arms they called it and a 
view of the villages up there a little - oh there's some such pretty cottages up there. Much much prettier. I think the old people had an eye for beauty much more than the younger generation. Oh I can picture those little cottages all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 snug}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589  in - in - agains
t the mountain you know, and lovely trees round them. Oh it is a shame really to - for - you know, to get them down. But they intended - you see there's no sewerage here and then they wanted to get the - village all compact ready for the - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 It's difficult being hilly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
It's difficult. Yes. That's it. To put in all that, yes - but - I - I never remember anything bad, you see, the - the - these pits, well actually they were so deep, and then people were so careful with the disinfectant and - ever
ything like that, I - I never remember - nasty smells because sometimes you get nasty smells with the drains now, that are really offensive don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Would there be epidemics of typhoid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No. No, I can never remember anything like that. There - 
I think it was only my brother and - and sister when they were very young, the twins had scarlet fever, I don't remember anybody else having that. And mam nursed them at home and the rest of us went down as I told you to Granny M.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 As you say it's so steep and so high up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. Yes. And of course they - an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 d apparently I think they caught}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589  it from Barry, being in Barry and there was some of them - you know. And I always remember when we were in Granny M's we used to sleep in one of the back bedrooms
, and it was such a thrill, see you could sort of step out of the back bedroom window onto the flat - we used to call it the flap, a little plateau; like before you start the mountain, and that's where we kiddies used to play. We used to call it the flat.
 
And we'd all have our different houses there made with stones, you know, bedrooms and kitchens and all that, we'd have all the old china that they didn't want at home, and then a few little currants and raisins, a bit of flour a drop of water and we'd - b
e doing all sorts there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Who would you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Well - people - children from round about, there were - we were only - our family was the largest in the - this little row. That's why I expect mam and dad were so lucky to have baby sitters isn't
 it. You see - yes, Auntie Cass just had the one, May, and Auntie Ann just Doris, one, so - and Auntie Poll and Uncle Bill, he was a colliery official, I think he was a manager of the Pont - one of the collieries in Pontypridd, so later on, just before we
 moved from there - they moved up to Pontypridd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Were you a little self-contained community, these five houses, or did you join in with the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh, join in quite a bit, oh they were lovely things in the chapels and all that in those days, you know, Band of Hope and }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 then they'd have these - little}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
 teas, you know - and vestry, and everybody would make their cake, their various cakes. One - one was very - well known for her rainbow cake. All that sort of thing. Yes. And then on the way up the hi
ll, just - I don't know - I was trying to picture in my mind - how exactly it was, it must have been a large bedroom, and these three bedrooms that I told you, these three houses that I told you on the way up the hill on the left - you just see the backs 
o
f them, and just the bedrooms. The fronts would be sort of out of sight - down below, and the - a large - it should have been - I should think it'd be two bedrooms, made into a little hall, and that was a gospel hall. And we all loved going there, you kno
w the type of thing don't you that they do there, at those meetings. They used to call them pen - something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Penny readings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Readings, that's right yes. Yes. And they'd be held - every week, one evening every week. And I'd go to that, all of us, 
yes. Oh it'd be full, they'd have a job - if you didn't go early you know you'd be - you'd be crowded out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Would you go to the ones only in your own chapel or would you go to anything in the village?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well anything, yes. The - and the - with the
 gymanfa ganu as I tell you they used to join - up all - Salem, our little chapel Salem now has been sold. And then they joined up, a few that were there joined up with Bethlehem. Yes. The independent, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What was Sunday like that, how did you spend Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Oh very quietly. Very very quietly. We'd often go to Maes Gwyn - when we were living in Brynn Terrace, I told you my aunt lived there didn't I, and my aunt - other aunt, the single one that wasn't married that used to help get in the water, 
we'd go down there and they had an organ and we came round singing hymns and that type of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What would you do on Sunday as a little girl? Would you go to chapel at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Go - yes, yes. But I don't remember us going to the morning service at all, it usually used to be a walk with dad on a Sunday morning, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Who would go then, all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Dad - all that could walk you see, quite a long walk, and a few of our little friends would love to come with us, 'cos dad would usually have something in his pockets, then he'd buy us something in the farm or - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 So you'd go out with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Be cooking the dinner, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Then we'd have - oh Sunday school. Oh yes. Compulsory that was, it wasn't - would you go, you just had to go. Yes. All of us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Where would you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Salom. Yes, Baptist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 English Baptist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No, Welsh. But quite a bit of English in the Sunday - Sunday school
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What would happen after Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Then home to tea. And probably we'd - take one or two little friends home to tea. Yes, not every Sunday, that'd be a little bit of a treat, but of course that stopped when Llewellyn got a bit bigger, mum felt
 that it embarrassed, I think you know for company. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What would you do then after }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 ea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Chapel. Yes. Yes. Go with mam and dad. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Would she take Llewellyn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No. No. Llewellyn didn't ever go, no, and then dad stayed home, dad - I d
on't think - I can't remember dad going to chapel. If it was it was very - you know, few times. Went - so then he stayed home to look after Llewellyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 But the same place of worship was it, Salom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 But your mother went just Sunday night did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. Only Sunday night, we - afternoon and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 The children went in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. And - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 But your mother went in the night and your father didn't go at all really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well he did when we were in Brynn Terrace, yes. Before Linnie - you know. Yes. That's it. Go then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Oh yes. There'd be the - go to Barry - Barry - not always, but when we went to Barry we had to clamber up the - do you know - do you know the woods o
n the side, you remember where the - viaduct was isn't it, well sort of about - when that works is now, we'd clamber right up there and catch the excursion - to the right of the viaduct. You know, that was a thrill, yes, that was the outing of the year. Y
es.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 All of you'd go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Would your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Yes. Until - and then - we used to arrange it then, leave someone - Llewellyn Because they'd take Llewellyn when he was younger mind, until it got noticeable he was mentally reta
rded, and - but then when it got later I stayed in quite a bit for mam and dad to go out for the rest. And - 'course my dad was - quite a - you know, took quite a - interest in public life, he was a chairman of the council I think for twenty years. And th
en he was on the Education Committee and - lots of things like that, so - and took a big interest in politics. And - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 I was going to ask you whether he took an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Did you talk much about politics in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Oh - ever such a lot, yes, and lots of people coming in, you've heard of W.C. Thomas haven't you, Willie Chard, oh he was - well you daren't mention my dad's name now. You see the tears come into this eyes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 W.C1 Thomas was one of the founders of the Miners Federation wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 That's - yes, he was one, yes, original yes, mm, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What would your father's views be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well - dad - Liberal, until - oh I'm trying to think now, when I started school at Pontypridd I - he was Liberal then, w
hy it stands out in my mind - I - palled up with a girlfriend there, Elsie Davis, and her dad was - the Member of Parliament for Pontypridd, and I was going around helping a bit with the meetings with the shorthand you know, to take some of the - things d
own you know, notes and that and take minutes and - I know I had to all sorts - of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589 \endash  not e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
xactly say lies - but shall I say white lies - because they were such staunch Labour people, and they had no room for anyone that was - I knew dad and mam were Liberal
 so I - I sort of - used to sort of get over that some way or other not to show - I was - sort of ashamed then that they weren't the same as them you know. And - but anyway, it couldn't have been very long afterwards that dad - turned - Labour. But I thin
k even to his very last day he was more Liberal really than Labour. Very like - right Labour not left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Why do you think he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well I think - the conditions of the working - people wasn't it, you know, sort of - because they had to 
work very very hard for small - I mean it - it might the way I've spoken might have sounded like that we were really affluent, but we weren't, it was just through my mother's thrift and my father's.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You were comparing it with other people at that time, there were some poorer families than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh very many. Very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 So comparatively speaking you weren't because your father was on the coal and earning quite well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes, that's it. Yes. Well yes, yes, or maybe not that he was earning much m
ore, but he was - looking after it, that's it, he didn't smoke or drink you see, and mam was very thrifty, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 And you say the house was cheap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. And then they had this built - this house built you see. Paid a mortgage on a mortgage I suppose and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 And I suppose your father wasn't out of work much was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Not unless in a strike. But he finished work very early mind, he was very young when he finished work. Oh he would have only been in his fifties, early fifties I would imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 But the period we're talking about he was working all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh yes. That's it, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What other social activities organised by the chapel did you take part in? You mentioned the little penny readings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. And Band of Hope. Band of Hope. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Was there a choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. A very nice choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Did you belong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Yes. I didn't have much of a voice so I wasn't much help. I - I think I had to follow - from the rest you know, if somebody went wrong I'd go wrong with them.
 I enjoyed it though very much, there was - another friend of my dad's then - Ben Rhys, I don't know if you've ever heard of him - have your heard of him, no. Not much older than me. Oh yes, he would have been. Oh yes, they would have been quite a bit old
er.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You were saying they were not allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Not allowed to speak English. You see, it was so difficult, they were brought up in all Welsh homes, both - both parents Welsh speaking, and then when they started school they couldn't speak English,
 they were put in front of the class, hat and cane, and - some board or something tied - around their necks. And that went on for quite a while in the Gwaelod school here apparently. So it was all English. So you can imagine it couldn't have been - a very
 good type of English could it for - coming from Welsh speaking homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well I've known some of the boys being put over the - across the desk and - you know, having - jolly good canings, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What about the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No. Canes on the hand and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What would you have to do to have a caning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Well you'd be - oh, if you be late for school. That was considered - and I suppose if you answered back or - did some of y
our lessons incorrectly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Do you ever remember being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Well, I was one of the lucky ones in school. I don't know why but I was. I - lots of people - my cousin, they used to say about Mr Long, oh that old bear, you know, but I always thoug
ht he was lovely. I suppose - if you get along fairly well with your lessons well you get along with the - with the teachers don't you, and I loved - as I tell you I loved school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes, quite a bit. I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Yes. And help with the homework always you know, yes, take a deep interest, yes. Yes. And dad started me with a little night school, and a professor was coming and giving lessons and he w
anted to train me to go to - for a scholarship for economics and that, but of course having - my brother -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What professor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. No, no. He was an English - an Englishman. Forget his name now. He - I'll tell you how - how they started, it was so
mething with the Co-operative movement started a night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh somewhere about fourteen - fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You had a little class in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes, in Taff's Well. Yes. Mm. And I went, yes, and I took a big interest in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 For how}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338984\charrsid6632589  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 long?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 And - oh I went for about two or three sessions. In and out, some evenings I couldn't get ready in time to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You didn't try an exam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 No, I couldn't, no, I was tied with - at home - I think my dad w
ould have loved me to mind and I think he coaxed my mother hard to have other help, I think it caused a little bit of friction between mam and dad. But mam - you know, wouldn't give in for me to - go to - college.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 This was very hard wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 What did you think at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
I think I was very disappointed and I know I was very disappointed when I passed - won the scholarship to go to Treforest and I couldn't go. Because most of my friends then they were - they were going there bu
t they'd failed the scholarship you see, they were - some of them were going on bursaries and - do you heard of the bursaries that they had in those times - and they would pay like Helena Phillips across the way there now - they were paying, they were qui
t
e - Nancy Milward - in the village here, that's another one that belonged to the Phillips - they all paid to go like I could have been going with them and not paying, you see I passed my - 'cos mam's health was very bad at the time, and having Lewellyn so
 
I stayed home to do lots of the housework. And man's health improved in a few months, I forget exactly how much, dad applied and someone else did to see if I could have my - you know, have my place there, but I couldn't because I'll tell you why, in the m
eantime - they'd given me another offer that they'd started - a form in one of the halls and that they had room. And mam refused and said it was impossible for me to go, so I think that was my last chance of -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Do you have any regrets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Oh yes. An
d the older I get the more - more regrets I have. And a little bitterness which I've never had. It seems sort of like a bit of a wasted life, do you know what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 You feel you had the ability?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Yes. Mm. Mm. And now my brain's gone too lazy now to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 But it was very difficult for your mother I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Yes, oh I don't hold a grudge against mam, not - not, not a bit, no. And I can't remember being bitter when I was young. But now and again it comes - you know, I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 It must have been very hard for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Mm. Mm. Oh I didn't have very easy definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11689985 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 
Did the children come from similar types of home to your own in the school, the first school you went to, it was the only school you went to wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6098658 EJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2111273\charrsid6632589 Only school, yes. No, I went to a commercial - when I was twelve, twelve or thirteen.
